<br>
Back to CoH, it has sooo many uses, apart from the simple one of summoning a groupmate back to your group from the zone line or from the bottom of a trap pit in lGuk or HS.  I've used it to help split spawns when no FDer was available, (COH'ing the puller, doesn't clear agro anymore, but since the object of that agro is now out of range, the mobs will start to head back to their spawn points, allowing the usual FD split em and tag em approach).  I've also used it to help drag corpses from KoS areas, where you can use a non-kos player to do the dragging, but where they would normally gain agro from attempting to drag a KoS corpse (this happens in a lot of the Velious zones, including PoG).  With CoH, you send in your puller, they start dragging while CoH timer is running, and (hopefully) you CoH them to safety before they are killed.  If they couldn't drag the corpse far enough, they camp out/back in, rinse repeat.<br>
 <p><b>Yarril</b><br>57th Mage on <i>Xev</i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscrubfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scrubfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 1:43:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1486.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> COH'ing the puller, doesn't clear agro anymore, but since the object of that agro is now out of range<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> they camp out/back in<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Just to clear up any misconception, CoH <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> does</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> clear aggro if the puller is far enough from the mage.  I often tell my CoH victims to run away from me.<br>
<br>
I used CoH and my bard as a CR team in Hate.  Bard sings locate corpse spamming /corpse until they are close enough to the corpse to start dragging it.  If the bard gets aggro, he runs away, and mage casts CoH.  Bard gets a heal and goes back and drags the corpse closer.  rinse/repeat until the corpse is in camp.  Never had to camp the bard ever.<br>
<br>
I've used it to split mobs with the bard as well, although a rooter would be better.  Bard/snarer/rooter aggros bunch of mobs, targeting the one they want.  When they get the mob to a spot where they want to kill it, they snare/root it and get CoHed by the mage.  Then go back or have someone positioned to pick off the snared/rooted mob and bring them back to camp.<br>
<br>
I think that the common consensus is indoors, the CoH victim has to be more then 100 feet away (DS cast range), outdoors they have to be more then 200 feet away (Malosini range).  So cast one of those spells and if you get an &quot;out of range&quot; message, you can CoH and clear aggro.<br>
<br>
One last note:  If CoH victim casts a DoT on the mob, the mob will reaggro on the victim as soon as the DoT pulses.  This can be good or bad, depending on what tactics you are using.<br>
<br>
